{{Infobox person | name = Kim Friedman | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birthname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1949|11|14}} | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} Death date then birth --> | death_place = | othername = | occupation = [[Television director]] and [[television producer|producer]] | yearsactive = 1977&ndash;2014 | spouse = | domesticpartner = | website = }}
'''Kim Friedman''' (born November 14, 1949) is an American [[television director]] and [[television producer|producer]].
Friedman's TV career began by directing 70 episodes of the sitcom, ''[[Mary Hartman, Mary Hartman]]'' for [[Norman Lear]]. She then moved on to directing the pilot for and episodes of ''[[Square Pegs]]'', followed by episodes of ''[[L.A. Law]]'', ''[[The Love Boat]]'', ''[[Dynasty (1981 TV series)|Dynasty]]'', ''[[A Different World (TV series)|A Different World]]'', ''[[Head of the Class]]'', ''[[Beverly Hills, 90210]]'', ''[[Babylon 5]]'', the ''[[Star Trek]]'' series, ''[[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine|Deep Space Nine]]'', ''[[Star Trek: Voyager|Voyager]]'', ''[[Lizzie McGuire]]'' and more.
She also directed the ABC movie ''Before and After''.
In 1988, Friedman was nominated for [[Primetime Emmy Award]] directing ''[[L.A. Law]]'' episode, "Handroll Express".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0295272/awards|title=Kim Friedman|website=IMDb|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref>
Along with her TV career, Kim directed theatre: including at [[Joe Papp]]'s [[The Public Theater]], [[New York Shakespeare Festival]], and at the Tiffany Theater in Los Angeles. Friedman has also directed theater in London, as well as producing and directing the docu series ''The Real Normal'' and ''Here Comes the Dress''.
==CrazyJewishMom==
In late 2014, Friedman's daughter Kate began using [[Instagram]] to document the "crazy" text messages that she receives from her mother on a daily basis.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://instagram.com/crazyjewishmom/|title=Crazy Jewish Mom (@crazyjewishmom) • Instagram photos and videos|website=instagram.com|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref> The account has since garnered more than 800,000 followers the account has garnered attention from many media outlets, including [[ABC News]], [[BuzzFeed]], and [[Yahoo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/mother-daughter-force-viral-instagram-crazy-jewish-mom-30548340|title=Video: Mother, Daughter Force Behind Viral Instagram 'Crazy Jewish Mom'|first=ABC|last=News|website=ABC News|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/morganshanahan/this-instagram-account-is-literally-your-mother|title=This Instagram Account Is Literally Your Mother|publisher=|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/parenting/this-crazy-jewish-mom-is-everyones-mom-109235609072.html|title=This 'Crazy Jewish Mom' Is Everyone's Mom|publisher=|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref>
